<dd><table width="675"><tr valign="TOP"><td width="8%"><font size="2"><a href="otd0708.htm">Jul <nobr> 08</a></font></td><td><font size="2">The San Francisco Giant�s Jim Ray Hart hit for the cycle (a single, double, triple and home run in one game). Hart became the first National League player in 59 seasons to collect six runs batted in (RBI) during a single inning. The Giants walloped the Atlanta Braves 13-0.</font></td><td width="8%" valign="TOP"><font size="2" color="AQUA">Ref: <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20041022121256/http://www.historychannel.com/">3</a></td></table>
